    // It must be non-decreasing in character value (0 to 1) OR non-increasing (1 to 0).
    // Form 1: $0^a 1^b$ (where $a+b=n$). Cohesive if $a \ge 0, b \ge 0$ AND ($a \le 1$ OR $b \le 1$).
    // Form 2: $1^a 0^b$ (where $a+b=n$). Cohesive if $a \ge 0, b \ge 0$ AND ($a \le 1$ OR $b \le 1$).

    // Case A: $0^a 1^b$ (where $a+b=n$).
    // Requires $a \le 1$ OR $b \le 1$.
    // A1: $a=n, b=0 \implies 0^n$. (Covered by Cost0)
    // A2: $a=0, b=n \implies 1^n$. (Covered by Cost1)
    // A3: $a=1, b=n-1 \implies 01^{n-1}$. Cost to achieve: $\text{Count of '1's in } s \text{ at position 0} + \text{Count of '0's in } s \text{ at positions } [1, n-1]$.
